[Black "Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{ Hello everyone, and welcome to my course: Lifetime repertoires: The Jobava London!  My name is Hans Niemann, and I'm really happy to bring this course to Chessable. You might know me as IM Hans Niemann, the streamer! But I've taken some time off on my streaming, to improve my game, and I'm a Grandmaster, rated 2640, now! I'm also the 2021 US Junior Champion and the winner of the 2021 World Open!  I'm going to be straight up with you all, I'm the World-leading expert on the Jobava London and the only top player who is playing this opening consistently at the highest level.   The ideas that I'm showing in this course are absolutely groundbreaking novelties, that completely change the theoretical understanding of this position. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4
{ This is going to be the starting position of the Jobava London where Black begins to deviate. Black has many different possibilities here so it's important to be familiar with the different structures that arise.  The Jobava London is an opening that I really love to play myself, and it's great to spread the beauty of the Jobava London and show everyone how great this opening is! It's a great surprise weapon because not a lot of your opponents are expecting this opening!   Throughout the course, I've twisted and improved the main lines of the Jobava London to make it an extremely lethal opening.  In this introduction, I want to hammer down that the best part of the Jobava London is its simplicity.   After studying this course, you are familiar with the general themes, and playing the Jobava London will feel like second nature. This completely takes away all the burden of memorizing all the different lines!  I'm looking forward to seeing you in the next chapters! }
*

