8. Nb5 c4 9. a4 Bd7 10. c3 Bxb5 11. axb5 Qxb5
{ The natural move would be to protect the pawn but if you're saccing one pawn, why not another? }
12. Be2 { Yet again Black is forced to play a move that isn't very natural. }
12... Ne4
{ There are many options here but I like Nd2 as it challenges Black to make a few difficult decisions. }
13. Nd2 Nxd2 14. Qxd2
{ Choosing a square for the queen is very difficult as understanding the difference is even hard to understand with the help of computers. }
14... Qc6 15. e4
{ e4 is a very strong move, White must open the position immediately while the black king is still in the center or the compensation will be diluted. }
15... dxe4 16. Qe3 Be7 17. f3 O-O 18. fxe4
{ White has a strong center and the two bishops. Black's extra a7-pawn is more of an afterthought. }
