7... Bg6 8. Bg2
{ You'll notice a common theme of the light-squared bishop being a central target in Black's position starting from 3...Bf5. The concept of g4 and h4 makes things very difficult for this bishop. }
8... Nbd7 9. h4
{ The g6-bishop is in serious trouble. Black's usual response to g4 and h5 is to play ...h6 or ...h5 but the bishop is currently attacked so Black must get creative to save this bishop. }
9... Nxe5 10. dxe5 Ne4 11. Bxe4 Bxe4 12. f3 d4
{ The bishop is finally free but at the cost of a pawn and the initiative. }
13. exd4 Bxc3+ 14. bxc3 Bd5
{ After a continuation of only moves the variation continues. But again, I think we can conclude that it's very difficult for Black to play. }
15. Qd3 c5 16. c4 Bc6 17. dxc5 Qa5+ 18. Bd2 Qxc5 19. Qc3
{ I've lost count of how many only moves Black has had to make and I think that reflects the status of the position. }
