{ Crazy complications ensue immediately. Although the computer gives zeros everywhere, having more knowledge here will give you a significant advantage over your opponent.   4.e3  is the main move but it gives Black many options that are okay. I prefer to take a more direct approach and put Black to the test. }
4... Nxe4
{ 4...Nxe4 is arguably the best in response to 3.e4 as it leads to a somewhat dry endgame. However, I've analyzed this endgame very deeply and it is pleasant for White and very easy to play. Let's see how things progress. }
5. Nxe4 dxe4 6. dxc5
{ There are many interesting options here but 6...Qa5 is the most natural by far. }
6... Qa5+ 7. c3 Qxc5 8. Qa4+ Nc6 9. Qxe4 Bf5
{ 9...Bf5 is a very natural alternative to 9...g6 and a move that I faced. However, it is a mistake and allows White to have an edge. }
10. Qa4 Qb6 11. O-O-O
{ Castles is critical. Black's king is still in the center and White has a strong initiative. }
