{ Black can try to put some pressure but White can easily consolidate. } 7...
Qa5 8. Bd3 c5 9. Bxa6
{ Interestingly enough, we have provoked the move ...c5. We could have captured on a6 a move earlier but now Black is forced to give up the c5-pawn or double the a-pawns, both of which are not ideal. }
9... bxa6 10. Be5
{ Black's pawn structure is in ruins and the bishop on e5 is extremely strong. Not only does it control the g7-bishop, it also prevents ...Rb8 so b2 isn't that weak. }
