10... b5 11. Qd4
{ Qd4 is extremely strong and forces ...Rg8, so Black will not be able to castle. }
11... Rg8 12. Nc3 a5 13. c6 { c6 puts Black under direct pressure. } 13... axb4
14. Nxb5 Nf6 15. c7 Qe7 16. exd5 exd5+ 17. Ne2
{ This is an example of the ridiculous complications that can ensue. White still has an advantage. I don't think it's necessary to go any farther but I suppose one should be aware of the potential complications.  The good thing is that White is favored with the large majority, especially as you'll most likely know much more about the positions than your opponent. }
