{ It seems like the a4-knight is some trouble but c4 is extremely strong as it protects the knight and puts pressure on Black's center. }
11... Bc6 12. Rh3
{ It is always time for a rook lift. The position is equal objectively, but White maintains attacking chances and Black has a small margin of error. }
