6. h4
{ Black must immediately create counterplay on the queenside before they are overwhelmed on the kingside. }
6... b5 7. Bg2 g6
{ ...g6 is very logical because you want to have ...Nh5 in response to g5. White has a very thematic idea here. }
8. Qf3 Nbd7 9. Qg3 c5
{ The queen and bishop are a very strong combo. White is ready to finish development. }
10. Bc7 Qe7 11. a3
{ Prophylaxis is very important: ...cxd4 followed by ...Qb4 was a potential idea.  The position is equal according to the computer but from a practical perspective, I have no idea what Black should do.  Black's pieces are very restricted by the bishop on c7 and you can't really play ...Bg7 and castles because of Bd6. Therefore, White can freely finish development and add more pressure. }
