[Black "Pirc – 5.Be2 O-O 6.O-O e5 #1/4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 g6
{ White has many ways to secure a comfortable advantage. Although the central focus of the Moke London is 3.Bf4, it is important to note that this isn't forced and that White has different options. }
3. e4 d6
{ There are so many different setups for White here but I prefer to keep it simple. }
4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Be2
{ This might not be the most eye-catching idea, but White has a very simple plan in mind. It is clear that White has central control as the d4- and e4-pawns remain uncontested. White will simply complete development and show that Black's position is inferior. }
5... O-O 6. O-O
{ Black has many different setups here so it's important to know how to respond appropriately but the ideas are more or less the same. I would say that this is the first critical position in this line and I have shown how to react against the main moves. Some lines are very concrete, but in most of the lines, it's important to know the developmental plans. }
6... e5
{ I would say that 6...e5 is a critical move because Black is directly challenging the center. It is important to respond with a precise sequence of moves to punish Black! }
7. dxe5
{ I have faced this line many times with White and I've learned that it is crucial to take on e5. From an objective perspective, it is also the top computer line by far.  From a psychological perspective, you take your opponent out of their comfort zone: many Modern players tend to like complex tactical battles but you're going straight for an endgame. }
7... dxe5 8. Nxe5
{ Interestingly enough, 8.Nxe5 is the 2nd most common move and hasn't been played by anyone over 2400. However, it is the top choice of the engine by far and puts significant pressure on Black! }
8... Nxe4 9. Nxe4 Bxe5
{ ...Bxe5 immediately might seem natural but it is a mistake and White is able to seize the initiative. }
10. Bg5 Qxd1 11. Raxd1 Kg7
{ Black should have taken the pawn to have any chance to equalize, as now White retains an advantage. }
12. c3
{ f4 will come next and the bishop on e5 will be taken. Once the bishop pair is acquired, Black's dark squares will be very weak for the rest of the game. }
