{ This c6 structure is sort of trendy and I've played it quite a bit in online blitz but h3 is very difficult to face. }
4... d5 5. e5
{ White secures a space advantage and the inclusion of h3 prevents ...Bg4! }
5... f6 6. Bd3
{ I would like to note that there are only 11 games in the database here so it's not absolutely critical but the ideas are important to know here. }
6... fxe5 7. dxe5 Nh6 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1
{ I feel comfortable concluding it here but leaving you with a detailed positional explanation of what we're trying to achieve here.  First of all, the main part of our advantage lies in the g7-bishop which is currently hitting concrete. Secondly, Black's kingside is a bit tender. The point is to retain this positional control while completing developing and bringing more pieces to the kingside. Maneuvering the knight from b1 to g3 is a possible idea. }
