{ Black has two main choices here. They can immediately challenge the center or finish development.   3.c4  would transpose into the Benko and Modern Benoni which would warrant 2 additional courses. Regardless of this,  3.Nc3  is the best move. }
3... e6 4. e4 d6
{ This is quite rare in the database but it has been played by a few strong players. There are many ways to get an advantage but I have suggested the simplest. }
5. dxe6 Bxe6 6. Nge2
{ The knight will come to f4 where it will put pressure on the e6-bishop and control the d5 outpost. }
6... Nc6 7. Nf4 Be7 8. Nxe6 fxe6 9. g3
{ The bishop is ready to come to h3 with tempo, castles will follow. White's position is just amazing. }
9... d5
{ One should not that Black can try to take control in the center but with precise play White retains a huge advantage. }
10. exd5 Nxd5 { Nxd5 is preferred but this leaves the isolated e6-pawn. } 11.
Ne4
{ White has the beautiful e4 outpost, the bishop pair, and a clear target on e6. }
