[Black "Englund Gambit with 3...f6 #1/2"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 e5
{ The Grandmaster in me wanted to completely ignore the move 1...e5 as the computer gives a +2 advantage and I could never imagine an opponent of mine playing this in a classical game.  However, as a man of the people and this being a Lifetime Repertoire, I want to show how to crush the heart and soul of every Englund Gambit player.  Playing 1...e5 is truly a disease that stunts a player's development so I hope that if you crush someone here that you will give them a reality check and save them from the Englund Gambit cult. }
2. dxe5 Nc6 { 2...d6  3.Nf3  Nc6  transposes to the text move. } 3. Nf3
{ I will treat this as the starting position as other moves than 2...Nc6 end up transposing. Black has a few different setups here so it's important to be precise to fully punish our opponents. }
3... f6 4. e4 { Why take the pawn when you can take the initiative instead! }
4... Nxe5
{ 4...Nxe5 has been played 50 times and this is an example of the type of players who play the Englund. }
5. Nxe5 fxe5 6. Qh5+ g6 7. Qxe5+ Qe7 8. Qxh8
{ An Englund player might try to convince that this is a rook sacrifice, but that would only convince you of their madness. }
